      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:3:3:40:1",
      "text": [
        " الْمَشْيُ خَلْفَ الْجَنَازَةِ أَفْضَلُ مِنَ الْمَشْيِ بَيْنَ يَدَيْهَا ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad, from Muhammad Bin Ismail, from Muhammad Bin Uzafir, from Is’haq Bin Ammar, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘The walking behind the coffin is superior than the walking in front of it’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "1. Muhammad ibn Yahya has narrated from Ahmad ibn Muhammad from Muhammad ibn Isma’il from Muhammad ibn ‘Adhafir from Ishaq ibn ‘Ammar, who has said the following: “Abu ’Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘Walking behind the coffin of the deceased is more virtuous than walking in front of it.’” "
        ]
      }
